This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a novel approach that combines Model-free Reinforcement Learning (MFRL) and Model-based Reinforcement Learning (MBRL) to achieve high performance with a small amount of data. The paper also mentions the use of Model Predictive Control (MPC) which is a popular control technique in Robotics (cs.RO) and Autonomous Systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper's focus on exploration and planning aligns with the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper's use of continuous control benchmarks suggests a possible connection to Computer Vision (cs.CV) as well.
